S074.Q1. HOW OLD WERE YOU ON YOUR LAST BIRTHDA?  1. 18-19 YEARS 2. 20 3. 21-24 4. 25-27 5. 28-29 6. 30-34 7. 35 YEARS AND OVER 8. NO ANSWER

S074.Q5. WHERE DID YOU LIVE MOST OF THE TIME BEFORE YOU WERE 16 YEARS OL?  1. ON A FARM OR IN THE COUNTRY 2. IN A SMALL TOWN (FEWER THAN 2,500 PEOPLE) 3. IN A TOWN (WITH BETWEEN 2,500 AND 25,000 PEOPLE) 4. IN A CITY (BETWEEN 25,000 AND 100,000 PEOPLE) 5. IN A LARGE CITY (MORE THAN 100,000 PEOPLE) 0. NO ANSWER

YES, BECAUSE OF DEPENDENTS WHO NEEDED MY SUPPORT 04. YES, BECAUSE OF THE IMPORTANCE OF MY JOB 05. YES, BECAUSE OF MY HEALTH OR PHYSICAL CONDITION 06. YES, BECAUSE OF SOME OTHER REASON 07. A COMBINATION OF 3 AND 4 08. A COMBINATION OF 4-5 09. A COMBINATION OF 3-4-5 10. A COMBINATION OF 3-5 11. NO ANSWER 00. NO CODE OR NO DATA

S074.Q9. IN GENERAL, HOW WELL DO YOU THINK THE ARMY IS RU?  1. IT IS RUN VERY WELL 2. IT IS RUN PRETTY WELL 3. IT IS NOT RUN SO WELL 4. IT IS RUN VERY POORLY 5. UNDECIDED 0. NO ANSWER
S074.Q10. HOW MUCH OF YOUR TRAINING OR DUTY TIME IS USED IN DOING THINGS THAT DO NOT SEEM IMPORTANT TO YO?  1. A LOT OF IT 2. SOME OF IT 3. ONLY A LITTLE OF IT 4. NONE OF IT 0. NO ANSWER
S074.Q11. DO YOU USUALLY FEEL THAT WHAT YOU ARE DOING IN THE ARMY IS WORTHWHILE OR NO?  1. I USUALLY FEEL IT IS NOT WORTHWHILE 2. I USUALLY FEEL IT IS WORTHWHILE 3. UNDECIDED 0. NO ANSWER

S074.Q14. IN GENERAL, HOW WOULD YOU SAY YOU FEEL MOST OF THE TIME, IN GOOD SPIRITS OR IN LOW SPIRIT?  1. I AM USUALLY IN GOOD SPIRITS 2. I AM IN GOOD SPIRITS SOME OF THE TIME AND IN LOW SPIRITS SOME OF THE TIME 3. I AM USUALLY IN LOW SPIRITS 0. NO ANSWER

S074.Q19. IF IT WERE UP TO YOU TO CHOOSE, WOULD YOU RATHER BE A SOLDIER OR WOULD YOU RATHER BE A CIVILIAN DOING SOME KIND OF WORK NEEDED TO WIN THE WA?  1. I WOULD RATHER BE A SOLDIER 2. I WOULD RATHER BE A CIVILIAN DOING SOME KIND OF WORK NEEDED TO WIN THE WAR 3. UNDECIDED 0. NO ANSWER

S074.Q23C. SINCE YOU HAVE BEEN IN THE ARMY, WHAT ONE SPORT HAVE YOU MOST OFTEN TAKEN PART IN DURING YOUR OFF-DUTY FREE TIM?  1. "B" SPORT MENTIONED 2. "X" SPORT MENTIONED 3. I HAVE NOT TAKEN PART IN ANY SPORTS 4. NAMES SOME OTHER SPORT THAN THOSE IN CODES 1 AND 2 5. COMBINATION OF 1 AND 2 0. NO ANSWER P. THE NEXT FEW QUESTIONS ABOUT HEALTH AND DEVELOPMENT ARE VERY IMPORTANT TO THE ARMY. ANSWER EACH ONE CAREFULLY EVEN THOUGH SOME OF THEM MAY SOUND STRANGE OR EVEN USELESS TO YOU. THESE FACTS ARE GREATLY NEEDED BY MEDICAL EXAMINERS FOR PROPER TREATMENT OF MEN WHO NEED HELP IN MEETING THE PROBLEMS OF ARMY LIFE AND IN CLASSIFICATION OF MEN AT INDUCTION STATIONS. WHEN THE ANSWERS OF TYPICAL MEN ARE KNOWN, IT WILL BE POSSIBLE TO GIVE MORE EFFECTIVE HELP TO THOSE SOLDIERS WHO HAVE SPECIAL PROBLEMS.
